<title>Manage program stages</title>
    <section>
        <title>About program
            <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161005T101348+0200" comment="At next revision, add more infor in the about section."?>stages<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
        <para>A program consist of program stages. A program stage defines which actions should be
            taken at each stage.</para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Create a program stage</title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Program / Attributes</emphasis> app and click
                        <emphasis role="bold">Program</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click the program you want to add a program stage to and select <emphasis
                        role="bold">View program stages</emphasis>.</para>
                <para>A list of existing stages for the selected program opens. If the program
                    doesn't have any program stages, the list is empty.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Add new</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Enter program stage details:</para>
                <orderedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Enter a <emphasis role="bold">Name</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Enter a <emphasis role="bold">Description</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>In the <emphasis role="bold">Scheduled days from start</emphasis>
                            field, enter the minimum number of days to wait for starting the program
                            stage.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </orderedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Enter repeatable program stage details.</para>
                <orderedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Specify if the program stage is <emphasis role="bold"
                                >Repeatable</emphasis> or not.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Select a <emphasis role="bold">Period type</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Enter <emphasis role="bold">Standard interval days</emphasis>.</para>
                        <para>The number of days
                            t<?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161004T172357+0200" comment="After you repeat a program stage?"?>o
                            repea<?oxy_comment_end?>t the repeatable program stage.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161004T172533+0200" comment="At next release: Review para."?>
                        <para>Clear <emphasis role="bold">Display generate event box after
                                completed</emphasis> if you don&apos;t want to display <emphasis
                                role="italic">Create new event box</emphasis> to create new event
                            for a repeatable stage after you click <emphasis role="italic"
                                >Complete</emphasis> for an event of the stage in data entry form.
                            This field is select by default.</para>
                        <?oxy_comment_end?>
                    </listitem>
                </orderedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Enter form
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161004T173652+0200" comment="Before release: review this sub-list
Consider turning it into a table."?>details<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">Auto-generate event</emphasis></para>
                        <para>Clear this to prevent for creating an event of this program stage
                            automatically when a entity enroll into the program.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">Open data entry form after
                            enrollment</emphasis></para>
                        <para>Automatically open the event of this stage as soon as the entity has
                            enrolled into the program.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">Report date to use</emphasis></para>
                        <para>The date is used for report date of the event opened automatically.
                            There are two options , include <emphasis role="italic">Incident
                                date</emphasis> or <emphasis role="italic">Enrollment
                                date</emphasis>. </para>
                        <para>If the Report date to use is selected as one of those
                            two(&apos;incident date&apos;/&apos;enrollment date&apos;), in
                            Dashboard, the &apos;Report date&apos; of the event will be set as one
                            of those two. </para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">Block entry form after
                            completed</emphasis></para>
                        <para>Check on it for blocking entry form after completed the event of this
                            stage. The data values in the entry form cannot be changed until the
                            status of the event is reset as incomplete.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">Ask user to complete program when stage is
                                completed</emphasis></para>
                        <para>If this property is set, a popup will come up to ask if user wants to
                            create the event of next stage.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">Ask user to create new event when stage is
                                complete</emphasis></para>
                        <para>If this property is set, a popup will come up to ask if user wants to
                            create a new event of this stage when an event of this stage completed.
                            This property is active only when Repeatable field is set.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">Generate events by enrollment
                            date</emphasis></para>
                        <para>Check on it for auto-generating due dates of events from
                            program-stages of this program based on the enrollment date. If it is
                            not checked, the due dates are generated based on incident date.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">Capture coordinates</emphasis></para>
                        <para>Many types of events may be recorded at a facility or be <emphasis
                                role="italic">owned-by</emphasis> a health worker at a facility, but
                            actually take place somewhere in the community. This field is checked to
                            get coordinates of the place.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">Complete allowed only if validation
                                passes</emphasis></para>
                        <para>The event created by this program stage is completed only when all
                            validation rules are passed.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Select if you want to <emphasis role="bold">Pre-generate event
                                UID</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="italic">Description of report date</emphasis> - The
                            description for report date which is displayed in case entry
                            form.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Assign data
                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161004T173029+0200" comment="At next revision: Review list item"?>elements<?oxy_comment_end?>:</para>
                <orderedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>In the list of <emphasis role="bold">Available data
                                elements</emphasis>, double-click the data elements you want to
                            assign to the program stage.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>For each assigned data element, review the properties. You can
                            select:</para>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para><emphasis role="bold">Compulsory</emphasis></para>
                                <para>The value of this data element must be filled into data entry
                                    form before completing the event.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161004T161324+0200" comment="More info needed."?>
                                <para><emphasis role="bold">Allow provided
                                    elsewhere</emphasis></para>
                                <?oxy_comment_end?>
                                <para>Specify if the value of this data element comes from other
                                    facility, not in the facility where this data is entered.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para><emphasis role="bold">Display in reports</emphasis></para>
                                <para>Display the value of this data element into the
                                    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161004T173000+0200" comment="In Event Capture app?"?>single
                                    event without registration<?oxy_comment_end?> data entry
                                    function.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161004T161334+0200" comment="More info needed."?>
                                <para><emphasis role="bold">Date in future</emphasis></para>
                                <?oxy_comment_end?>
                                <para>Allow to select a date in future for date data
                                    elements.</para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </listitem>
                </orderedlist>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Add</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Create a program stage
            <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161005T110201+0200" comment="You can also Edit, translate remove and show details."?>section<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Program / Attributes</emphasis> app and click
                        <emphasis role="bold">Program</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click the program you want to add a program stage section to and select
                        <emphasis role="bold">View program stages</emphasis>.</para>
                <para>A list of existing stages for the selected program opens. If the program
                    doesn't have any program stages, the list is empty.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click a program stage and select <emphasis role="bold">Section
                        management</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Add new</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Enter a program stage section <emphasis role="bold">Name</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the list of <emphasis role="bold">Available data elements</emphasis>,
                    double-click the data elements you want to assign to the program stage
                    section.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>In the list of <emphasis role="bold">Available indicators</emphasis>,
                    double-click the indicators you want to assign to the program stage
                    section.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Add</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
